ansfer","Multiple pregnancy","Pelvic haemorrhage","Uterine perforation","Ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMultiple pregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E is a significant risk of IVF that affects both mother and babies. For the mother, multiple pregnancy increases the risk of gestational diabetes, pre-eclampsia, and caesarean delivery. For the babies, risks include preterm birth, low birth weight, and developmental complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other complications listed affect only the mother:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInfection at embryo transfer\u003C/strong\u003E - A rare complication that can cause maternal pelvic infection\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPelvic haemorrhage\u003C/strong\u003E - Can occur during egg collection, affecting only maternal health\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUterine perforation\u003C/strong\u003E - A rare procedural complication during embryo transfer\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOvarian hyperstimulation syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E - Affects only the mother due to ovarian stimulation medications\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile multiple pregnancy rates have decreased with single embryo transfer policies, it remains an important consideration when counselling patients about IVF risks.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The risk of multiple pregnancy is increased in IVF pregnancies and carries increased risks for both mother and babies","Multiple pregnancy complications include increased risk of preterm birth, pre-eclampsia, and gestational diabetes"],"references":["Wang J, Sauer MV. In vitro fertilization (IVF): a review of 3 decades of clinical innovation and technological advancement. Ther Clin Risk Manag. 2006 Dec;2(4):355-64. doi: 10.2147/tcrm.2006.2.4.355. PMID: 18360648; PMCID: PMC1936357","Choe J, Shanks AL. In Vitro Fertilization. [Updated 2023 Sep 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK562266/","Singh K, Dewani D. Recent Advancements in In Vitro Fertilisation. Cureus. 2022 Oct 10;14(10):e30116. doi: 10.7759/cureus.30116. PMID: 36381837; PMCID: PMC9644046"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60749"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15756"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60749","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60749"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T13:32:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T13:32:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8447"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75241"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"sel